WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.136 --> 00:00:12.303 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER A]
This announcement is for

00:00:12.387 --> 00:00:16.766 position:50% align:center
all of our beloved
Illusory Country citizens.

00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:20.729 position:50% align:center
It's nearly 11 PM,
the hour of the rat.

00:00:20.812 --> 00:00:22.647 position:50% align:center
All citizens without
special permission

00:00:22.731 --> 00:00:24.399 position:50% align:center
must return home at this time.

00:00:24.482 --> 00:00:27.569 position:50% align:center
We greatly appreciate
your cooperation.

00:00:27.652 --> 00:00:28.737 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN A]
Hear that?

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:29.946 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN B]
Yeah. That sucks for Hakata.

00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.531 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN C]
Damn the True Army!

00:00:31.614 --> 00:00:33.908 position:50% align:center
They think they have
the run of the place!

00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:36.911 position:50% align:center
Shit, what are the
higher-ups thinking?

00:00:36.995 --> 00:00:39.539 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN A] Well, I'm thinking
the era of idols is done-zies.

00:00:39.622 --> 00:00:40.790 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN C]
Don't be stupid!

00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:42.667 position:50% align:center
As long as they have fans
who support them,

00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:44.294 position:50% align:center
idols will never die out!

00:00:44.377 --> 00:00:47.255 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Exactly! It's not over!

00:00:50.091 --> 00:00:52.594 position:50% align:center
You still have an idol.

00:00:54.888 --> 00:00:55.930 position:50% align:center
And she's right here!

00:00:56.014 --> 00:00:58.600 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:00:58.683 --> 00:01:00.435 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] The Little Animals
of Fortune Idol Group

00:01:00.518 --> 00:01:03.063 position:50% align:center
will hop above the status quo!

00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:06.191 position:50% align:center
Rabbit Foot...
reporting for duty!

00:01:06.274 --> 00:01:08.443 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:01:08.526 --> 00:01:11.279 position:50% align:center
Alrighty, you honey-bunnies!
You know the drill!

00:01:11.363 --> 00:01:12.447 position:50% align:center
One, two, three!

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:16.618 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Rabbit! Foot! Love! Whoo!

00:01:17.577 --> 00:01:19.120 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
That was great, everyone!

00:01:19.204 --> 00:01:20.288 position:50% align:center
So here's the thing,

00:01:20.372 --> 00:01:22.165 position:50% align:center
the True Army arrested
the other members,

00:01:22.248 --> 00:01:24.584 position:50% align:center
leaving me all by my lonesome.

00:01:24.668 --> 00:01:28.338 position:50% align:center
But it's okay! That just
makes me a solo artist now!

00:01:28.421 --> 00:01:31.508 position:50% align:center
Name's Yuki Aoba!
Yuki-rin works, too!

00:01:31.591 --> 00:01:33.635 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheers]

00:01:33.718 --> 00:01:37.722 position:50% align:center
[giggles] Without
further ado... Ready?

00:01:37.806 --> 00:01:40.308 position:50% align:center
Let's make it hoppin'!

00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:43.645 position:50% align:center
[YUKI screams]

00:01:43.728 --> 00:01:45.605 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN A]
Protect Yuki-rin!

00:01:46.523 --> 00:01:47.774 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN B]
As long as we have her,

00:01:47.857 --> 00:01:49.901 position:50% align:center
we still have our dreams.

00:01:49.984 --> 00:01:52.987 position:50% align:center
Huh? What's going on?

00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:55.740 position:50% align:center
[gasps, screams]

00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:29.709 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Thanks to Shark One's victory,

00:03:29.793 --> 00:03:31.711 position:50% align:center
Akihabara was saved.

00:03:31.795 --> 00:03:35.507 position:50% align:center
However, due to the tremendous
levels of passion she exuded,

00:03:35.590 --> 00:03:39.886 position:50% align:center
Rin Akagi fell victim
to severe burnout.

00:03:39.969 --> 00:03:42.806 position:50% align:center
Rest is essential
for battery girls.

00:03:42.889 --> 00:03:46.059 position:50% align:center
She must recharge her heart,
as well as her mind.

00:03:46.142 --> 00:03:52.607 position:50% align:center
Za-za-za-za-za. Za-za-za-Zabuh!
Za-za-za-za-za. Za-za-za-Zabuh!

00:03:52.691 --> 00:03:54.401 position:50% align:center
This is effective?

00:03:54.484 --> 00:03:56.444 position:50% align:center
Her heart powers the Garanndoll.

00:03:56.528 --> 00:03:59.155 position:50% align:center
That machine literally
runs on her passion.

00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.949 position:50% align:center
The most efficient
way to recharge her

00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:03.284 position:50% align:center
is to expose her to
whatever it is she enjoys.

00:04:03.368 --> 00:04:05.787 position:50% align:center
Meaning, commercials
for TV shows?

00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:07.539 position:50% align:center
[MIMI] Make do with what
you have, you know?

00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:10.709 position:50% align:center
So you're saying she's
always been a ditz?

00:04:10.792 --> 00:04:15.714 position:50% align:center
Well, whenever she overexerts
herself, her brain suffers.

00:04:15.797 --> 00:04:17.132 position:50% align:center
It turns to straight mush!

00:04:17.215 --> 00:04:21.386 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC] That's right!
It's like a bowl of oatmeal!

00:04:21.469 --> 00:04:23.013 position:50% align:center
This state is just scary.

00:04:23.096 --> 00:04:24.431 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
You think?

00:04:24.514 --> 00:04:27.183 position:50% align:center
So, hey, if we're sans
battery girl when they attack,

00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:28.810 position:50% align:center
aren't we in trouble?

00:04:28.893 --> 00:04:31.021 position:50% align:center
Thankfully, we're one
step ahead of you.

00:04:31.104 --> 00:04:32.397 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:35.734 position:50% align:center
She should be here by now.
The second battery girl.

00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:37.902 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Huh?

00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:38.611 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:39.529 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE cheering]

00:04:39.612 --> 00:04:41.156 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI, MUNAKATA]
Huh?!

00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:44.868 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE]
Yuki-rin!

00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:47.871 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Hi! We're the Little
Animals Idol Group!

00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:51.041 position:50% align:center
But you all know us
as Rabbit Foot!

00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:53.793 position:50% align:center
My name is Yuki Aoba!

00:04:53.877 --> 00:04:56.254 position:50% align:center
The last remaining
member is here to stay!

00:04:56.338 --> 00:04:58.214 position:50% align:center
So make some noise for her!

00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:01.051 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE cheering]

00:05:01.134 --> 00:05:02.844 position:50% align:center
Who is she?

00:05:02.927 --> 00:05:04.012 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Yuki-rin.

00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:06.765 position:50% align:center
An idol and a battery girl.
Double threat!

00:05:06.848 --> 00:05:07.724 position:50% align:center
--[MUNAKATA] Uh...
--[HOSOMICHI] Huh?

00:05:07.807 --> 00:05:10.310 position:50% align:center
Thanks oh-so-much
for having me!

00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:15.148 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC] Her potential
passion is extraordinary!

00:05:15.231 --> 00:05:16.399 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
You don't say...

00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.985 position:50% align:center
[UKAI] Got a lot of heart
for a 17-year-old.

00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:20.111 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI yelps]

00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:21.654 position:50% align:center
[UKAI]
She's keepin' the group alive

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:24.657 position:50% align:center
despite the other members
being sent off to Odaiba.

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:27.494 position:50% align:center
True Army got every last
one of 'em except her.

00:05:27.577 --> 00:05:28.703 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
And you are?

00:05:28.787 --> 00:05:30.789 position:50% align:center
Heh. Call me Ukai.

00:05:30.872 --> 00:05:33.792 position:50% align:center
I do everything from combat
training to gathering intel.

00:05:33.875 --> 00:05:36.961 position:50% align:center
Not a jack-of-all-trades,
the king! Dig?

00:05:37.045 --> 00:05:38.296 position:50% align:center
A king?

00:05:38.380 --> 00:05:42.008 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI] Yeah.
All hail king of the weirdos.

00:05:42.092 --> 00:05:45.303 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE cheers]

00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:50.100 position:50% align:center
Welcome, Yuki. Have you been
briefed on the current sitch?

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:51.643 position:50% align:center
Yes!

00:05:51.726 --> 00:05:54.062 position:50% align:center
When I was abducted by that
Ukai guy, I got the gist of it!

00:05:54.145 --> 00:05:54.938 position:50% align:center
Say what?

00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:56.981 position:50% align:center
She's feisty! Ha!

00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:58.650 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Why is he laughing?

00:05:58.733 --> 00:06:01.319 position:50% align:center
I've always been intrigued
by the resistance.

00:06:01.403 --> 00:06:04.614 position:50% align:center
So I would be tickled pink to
pilot your giant robot, sir!

00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:06.950 position:50% align:center
Music to my ears, young lady.

00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:08.785 position:50% align:center
You do know you'll be
risking your life.

00:06:08.868 --> 00:06:10.620 position:50% align:center
It's not some kind of game.

00:06:10.704 --> 00:06:12.080 position:50% align:center
I'm only acting so chipper

00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:14.374 position:50% align:center
'cause I'm excited to
protect our culture.

00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:15.875 position:50% align:center
Just like everyone here!

00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:18.169 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE]
Yeah!

00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:19.796 position:50% align:center
It's a perfect fit!

00:06:19.879 --> 00:06:23.341 position:50% align:center
Idols love making smiles.
It's our job to lift people up!

00:06:23.425 --> 00:06:24.759 position:50% align:center
So that's what I'll do!

00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:27.303 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
What wonderful words, Yuki-rin!

00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:28.847 position:50% align:center
They said that?

00:06:28.930 --> 00:06:31.433 position:50% align:center
Yes, and our leader is delighted
to hear you'll be our pilot.

00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:35.228 position:50% align:center
Huh? Your leader? So this
enormous plushie is...

00:06:35.311 --> 00:06:38.356 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Correct! The head honcho!

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:39.607 position:50% align:center
[YUKI squeals]

00:06:39.691 --> 00:06:41.109 position:50% align:center
[MUNAKATA chuckles]

00:06:41.192 --> 00:06:44.154 position:50% align:center
I look forward to
working with you!

00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:46.656 position:50% align:center
Nice to meet you. I'm Munakata.

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.992 position:50% align:center
You know, if you'll be
working as an idol here,

00:06:49.075 --> 00:06:50.285 position:50% align:center
you're gonna need a manager.

00:06:50.368 --> 00:06:51.828 position:50% align:center
Professionally speaking, yeah.

00:06:51.911 --> 00:06:53.246 position:50% align:center
Well, then,

00:06:53.329 --> 00:06:55.832 position:50% align:center
considering all my connections,
I'd be up for the task.

00:06:55.915 --> 00:06:58.877 position:50% align:center
I'm in good with everyone here,
and that includes Hosomichi.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:06:59.461 position:50% align:center
Small flex.

00:06:59.544 --> 00:07:00.587 position:50% align:center
Hosomichi?

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:02.797 position:50% align:center
There he is now! Yeah!

00:07:02.881 --> 00:07:05.550 position:50% align:center
We're so close he'd give me
a kidney if I asked him to.

00:07:05.633 --> 00:07:06.968 position:50% align:center
Or even an eyeball.

00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:09.346 position:50% align:center
Hey. You're not as
funny as you think.

00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:10.847 position:50% align:center
[MUNAKATA]
Can you stop being a sour puss

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:12.098 position:50% align:center
for, like, ten minutes?

00:07:12.182 --> 00:07:13.975 position:50% align:center
I mean, we're like in
the presence of an idol.

00:07:14.059 --> 00:07:17.312 position:50% align:center
Or perhaps, you're peeved at
the idea of working with her.

00:07:17.395 --> 00:07:19.522 position:50% align:center
You finally managed to
hit things off with Rin,

00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:21.858 position:50% align:center
now it feels like
you're cheating, right?

00:07:21.941 --> 00:07:24.569 position:50% align:center
That couldn't be
further from the truth.

00:07:24.652 --> 00:07:29.282 position:50% align:center
A job's a job.
I simply do what I'm told.

00:07:29.366 --> 00:07:32.952 position:50% align:center
There. You see just how friendly
and casual he is with me?

00:07:33.036 --> 00:07:34.996 position:50% align:center
I'd be an ideal manager for you!

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:36.706 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Umm... Hmm...

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.083 position:50% align:center
Ah!

00:07:39.501 --> 00:07:42.629 position:50% align:center
[YUKI humming]

00:07:42.712 --> 00:07:44.047 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:45.465 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:07:45.548 --> 00:07:49.427 position:50% align:center
If I can choose, I'd much
rather be managed by you!

00:07:49.511 --> 00:07:52.305 position:50% align:center
Fair, idols get
what they want.

00:07:52.389 --> 00:07:54.182 position:50% align:center
But I'll be the
head manager, okay?

00:07:54.265 --> 00:07:55.600 position:50% align:center
Huh?!

00:07:55.684 --> 00:07:57.268 position:50% align:center
We'll have a trial run once
they finish maintenance.

00:07:57.352 --> 00:08:00.647 position:50% align:center
Rest up until then!
Or whatever it is idols do.

00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:05.110 position:50% align:center
Heh. Good luck, manager.

00:08:06.194 --> 00:08:09.072 position:50% align:center
[sighs] Yeah, I hear ya.

00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:13.451 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Must be rough putting on

00:08:13.535 --> 00:08:14.619 position:50% align:center
such an energetic show

00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:16.705 position:50% align:center
immediately after
being kidnapped.

00:08:16.788 --> 00:08:18.289 position:50% align:center
You need a hug?

00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:19.958 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Oh, don't bother with that act.

00:08:20.041 --> 00:08:21.459 position:50% align:center
What?

00:08:21.543 --> 00:08:23.044 position:50% align:center
So what's the game plan?

00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:27.757 position:50% align:center
Wait, you-- Uh, sorry. What?

00:08:27.841 --> 00:08:32.762 position:50% align:center
C'mon! Idols have schedules,
you know! We work!

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:34.305 position:50% align:center
What kind of schedule?

00:08:34.389 --> 00:08:36.182 position:50% align:center
Meet-and-greets with the fans
along with signing sessions

00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:37.225 position:50% align:center
are, of course, a must.

00:08:37.308 --> 00:08:38.852 position:50% align:center
A radio show would be nice.

00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:41.021 position:50% align:center
Ooh! I'll have
concerts on the daily.

00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:42.939 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I'm gonna need
time to rehearse!

00:08:43.023 --> 00:08:45.817 position:50% align:center
And it's my job to
arrange all that?

00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:48.903 position:50% align:center
Duh, like, you want me
to fuel that mech, yeah?

00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:50.488 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow.

00:08:50.572 --> 00:08:54.075 position:50% align:center
You don't happen to have a split
personality by chance, do you?

00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:55.660 position:50% align:center
You're one to talk.

00:08:55.744 --> 00:08:58.997 position:50% align:center
I saw that mask you put on as
soon as the glasses came off.

00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:00.165 position:50% align:center
Who knew one accessory

00:09:00.248 --> 00:09:03.001 position:50% align:center
was the difference
between cool and fool?

00:09:04.085 --> 00:09:07.213 position:50% align:center
You and I are alike in that way,
so I won't judge too hard.

00:09:07.297 --> 00:09:08.840 position:50% align:center
Should even help us get along.

00:09:08.923 --> 00:09:11.843 position:50% align:center
And lead me down the path
to falling for you.

00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:14.346 position:50% align:center
The lies just keep on comin'.

00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:17.265 position:50% align:center
[YUKI chuckles]

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:18.767 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
That one was true,

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:22.020 position:50% align:center
as long as you stay
my loyal manager.

00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:23.980 position:50% align:center
--[snap]
--[HOSOMICHI grunts]

00:09:24.064 --> 00:09:26.358 position:50% align:center
All right, then!
It's time to work!

00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:28.401 position:50% align:center
You have five minutes to
fetch something soothing

00:09:28.485 --> 00:09:29.944 position:50% align:center
for my throat!

00:09:30.028 --> 00:09:32.530 position:50% align:center
Okay, fine! I'm going!

00:09:32.614 --> 00:09:33.782 position:50% align:center
Wear your glasses!

00:09:33.865 --> 00:09:36.618 position:50% align:center
I want a manager repping
me, not a sleazeball!

00:09:36.701 --> 00:09:38.912 position:50% align:center
They're on. Jeez!

00:09:40.330 --> 00:09:42.707 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
I have a manager.

00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:50.507 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
I'm Yuki! It's nice to meet you!

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:54.636 position:50% align:center
I have a little PSA for
you all today! Ta-da!

00:09:54.719 --> 00:09:55.720 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Huh?

00:09:55.804 --> 00:09:57.263 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Once upon a time,

00:09:57.347 --> 00:10:00.016 position:50% align:center
Rabbit Foot was the best group
of performers on the planet!

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:04.145 position:50% align:center
But A-chan, Riocchi,
Mona-pon, Nano-shi,

00:10:04.229 --> 00:10:06.147 position:50% align:center
and, uh, What's-her-face,

00:10:06.231 --> 00:10:10.068 position:50% align:center
the True Army found all five
of them and locked them away.

00:10:10.151 --> 00:10:15.031 position:50% align:center
Now I'm by myself in
this cruel, cold world.

00:10:16.741 --> 00:10:19.119 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE]
Yuki-rin!

00:10:19.202 --> 00:10:21.246 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
But I refuse to give up!

00:10:21.329 --> 00:10:23.707 position:50% align:center
I'll act as Arahabaki's
special teammate,

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:26.126 position:50% align:center
fighting alongside everybody
in the Garanndoll!

00:10:26.209 --> 00:10:27.544 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE cheering]

00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:29.879 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's powered by love,

00:10:29.963 --> 00:10:34.175 position:50% align:center
and there is nothing I love
more than being an idol!

00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:37.387 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE]
Yuki-rin!

00:10:37.470 --> 00:10:39.055 position:50% align:center
[CITIZENS]
Rabbit Foot!

00:10:39.139 --> 00:10:40.640 position:50% align:center
[RESISTANCE MEMBER A]
What?

00:10:40.724 --> 00:10:42.684 position:50% align:center
How'd a bunch of randos like you
manage to infiltrate our base?

00:10:42.767 --> 00:10:45.103 position:50% align:center
[CITIZEN A] No distance
can deter a true idol stan!

00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:46.312 position:50% align:center
