that same song.

00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:31.561 position:50% align:center
You must really like it.

00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:33.396 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
You're not wrong.

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:38.693 position:50% align:center
Ever hear of Yukiko
Aono? It's her song.

00:13:38.777 --> 00:13:40.612 position:50% align:center
I'd be super shocked
if you actually knew it

00:13:40.695 --> 00:13:42.739 position:50% align:center
since she only sings it live.

00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:45.533 position:50% align:center
It's like a secret
for hardcore fans.

00:13:45.617 --> 00:13:50.038 position:50% align:center
But it's important
to me. Very important.

00:13:50.121 --> 00:13:55.794 position:50% align:center
[YUKIKO singing in Japanese]

00:13:55.877 --> 00:13:58.713 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
I'll never forget...

00:13:58.797 --> 00:14:01.257 position:50% align:center
I saw her perform it at
concert I went to with my mom

00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:04.010 position:50% align:center
when I was a kid.

00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:05.970 position:50% align:center
I remember the lights.

00:14:06.054 --> 00:14:09.140 position:50% align:center
How the audience glowed
like a sea of stars.

00:14:09.224 --> 00:14:12.143 position:50% align:center
And at the center was
a girl everyone loved.

00:14:12.227 --> 00:14:14.979 position:50% align:center
[singing in Japanese]

00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:17.565 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
I wanted to be like her.

00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:23.113 position:50% align:center
But that's a thing of the past.
Thank you, True Army.

00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:25.073 position:50% align:center
Plus, Mom and Dad
were never onboard.

00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:27.617 position:50% align:center
You were blessed
with two wise parents.

00:14:27.701 --> 00:14:29.619 position:50% align:center
Even if I can't reach
Yukiko's level of fame,

00:14:29.703 --> 00:14:32.455 position:50% align:center
I refuse to watch
idols go extinct!

00:14:32.539 --> 00:14:33.707 position:50% align:center
That's why I'm here!

00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:35.041 position:50% align:center
If there are people
who want idols,

00:14:35.125 --> 00:14:36.835 position:50% align:center
then I'll be one for them!

00:14:36.918 --> 00:14:40.714 position:50% align:center
The perfect idol, Yuki Aoba.
One that everybody loves.

00:14:40.797 --> 00:14:42.799 position:50% align:center
Everybody? That sounds tough.

00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:44.300 position:50% align:center
Yeah, no kidding.

00:14:44.384 --> 00:14:47.721 position:50% align:center
How many stars had to ride
robots to gain their popularity?

00:14:47.804 --> 00:14:49.431 position:50% align:center
Obviously, the world sucks.

00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:52.017 position:50% align:center
So you're gonna power the
Garann dressed like that?

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:53.351 position:50% align:center
[YUKI giggles]

00:14:53.435 --> 00:14:55.729 position:50% align:center
